name: Lauren Boebert
summary: Republican Representative Lauren Boebert of Colorado has been diagnosed with May-Thurner syndrome, a condition that causes blood clots in the legs. The diagnosis came after she underwent surgery to remove a blood clot from her leg. Boebert, 36, is recovering from the surgery and is expected to make a full recovery. May-Thurner syndrome is caused by the compression of the left iliac vein, which is the main vein that carries blood from the left leg to the heart. The compression can lead to the formation of blood clots, which can be dangerous if they travel to the lungs (pulmonary embolism). The condition is more common in women than men and is often diagnosed in people between the ages of 20 and 40.
